lfstyl_group><wbmd_c_audnc_lfstyl object_type="wbmd_lookup" wbmd_lookup_type="consumer_audience_lifestyle" wbmd_storage_val="6" wbmd_disp_nm="Any"></wbmd_c_audnc_lfstyl></wbmd_c_audnc_lfstyl_group><wbmd_c_audnc_read_lvl_group><wbmd_c_audnc_read_lvl object_type="wbmd_lookup" wbmd_lookup_type="consumer_audience_reading_level" wbmd_storage_val="1" wbmd_disp_nm="Basic (high school)"></wbmd_c_audnc_read_lvl></wbmd_c_audnc_read_lvl_group><wbmd_c_audnc_ethn_group><wbmd_c_audnc_ethn object_type="wbmd_lookup" wbmd_lookup_type="consumer_audience_ethnicity" wbmd_storage_val="1" wbmd_disp_nm="All"></wbmd_c_audnc_ethn></wbmd_c_audnc_ethn_group><wbmd_c_tm_of_yr_group><wbmd_c_tm_of_yr object_type="wbmd_lookup" wbmd_lookup_type="consumer_time_of_year" wbmd_storage_val="5" wbmd_disp_nm="Any"></wbmd_c_tm_of_yr></wbmd_c_tm_of_yr_group><wbmd_c_clncl_tgt_pop_group></wbmd_c_clncl_tgt_pop_group><wbmd_c_art_thmbnl></wbmd_c_art_thmbnl><wbmd_c_channel_id></wbmd_c_channel_id><wbmd_c_frnd_nm>Cushings-Syndrome-Topic-Overview</wbmd_c_frnd_nm><wbmd_c_asset_name></wbmd_c_asset_name><wbmd_c_teaser>Topic Overview</wbmd_c_teaser><wbmd_c_mini_article object_type="wbmd_cons_shrt_txt" directive="expand" chronic_id="0000000000000000"></wbmd_c_mini_article></metadata_section><content_section><cons_import_health_ref><title>Topic Overview</title><pages><page><section_group><section_header></section_header><section_type>Overview</section_type><section_text><a name="hw71648"></a><h4>What is Cushing's syndrome?</h4><p>Cushing's syndrome is a
			 rare hormonal problem. It happens when there is too much of the
			 <a bookmark="stc15504-sec" document-type="Definition" href="/webmd/consumer_assets/controlled_content/healthwise/definition/Cortisol.xml" directive="friendlyurl" chronic_id="" object_type="" path="/webmd/consumer_assets/controlled_content/healthwise/definition/Cortisol.xml">hormone cortisol</a> in your body.</p><p>Normally,
			 cortisol levels increase through a chain reaction of hormones:</p><ol><li>First, the <a bookmark="sth150007-sec" document-type="Definition" href="/webmd/consumer_assets/controlled_content/healthwise/definition/Hypothalamus.xml" directive="friendlyurl" chronic_id="" object_type="" path="/webmd/consumer_assets/controlled_content/healthwise/definition/Hypothalamus.xml">hypothalamus</a> in the <a chronic_id="091e9c5e8041fa4e" crossLinkId="73853" directive="friendlyurl" externalId="091e9c5e8041fa4e" href="/webmd/consumer_assets/editorial/articles/image_collections/anatomy_pages/picture_of_the_brain.xml" keywordId="60487" keywordSetId="26677" object_type="wbmd_cons_article" path="/webmd/consumer_assets/editorial/articles/image_collections/anatomy_pages/picture_of_the_brain.xml">brain</a> makes a hormone called CRH
				(corticotropin-releasing hormone).</li><li> Then, CRH tells the pituitary
				gland to make another hormone called ACTH
				<a bookmark="sta123092-sec" document-type="Definition" href="/webmd/consumer_assets/controlled_content/healthwise/definition/ACTH.xml" directive="friendlyurl" chronic_id="" object_type="" path="/webmd/consumer_assets/controlled_content/healthwise/definition/ACTH.xml">(adrenocorticotropic hormone)</a>. </li><li> ACTH then
				tells the
				<a bookmark="sta123135-sec" document-type="Definition" href="/webmd/consumer_assets/controlled_content/healthwise/definition/Adrenal_glands_8428.xml" directive="friendlyurl" chronic_id="" object_type="" path="/webmd/consumer_assets/controlled_content/healthwise/definition/Adrenal_glands_8428.xml">adrenal glands</a> to make cortisol. Cortisol affects
				almost every area of the body. It is especially important in regulating <a chronic_id="091e9c5e8056ea80" crossLinkId="1506783" directive="friendlyurl" externalId="091e9c5e8056ea80" href="/webmd/consumer_assets/editorial/articles/image_collections/anatomy_pages/anatomy_picture_of_blood.xml" keywordId="62987" keywordSetId="28544" object_type="wbmd_cons_article" path="/webmd/consumer_assets/editorial/articles/image_collections/anatomy_pages/anatomy_picture_of_blood.xml">blood</a>
				pressure and
				<a bookmark="stm159337-sec" document-type="Definition" href="/webmd/consumer_assets/controlled_content/healthwise/definition/Metabolism.xml" directive="friendlyurl" chronic_id="" object_type="" path="/webmd/consumer_assets/controlled_content/healthwise/definition/Metabolism.xml">metabolism</a>.</li></ol><p>But if your body makes too much cortisol-or if you take
			 certain medicines that act like cortisol-you may start to have symptoms.
			 Cushing's syndrome may cause <a chronic_id="091e9c5e80046694" crossLinkId="440" directive="friendlyurl" externalId="091e9c5e80046694" href="/webmd/PageBuilder_Assets/scopemaps/WebMD Consumer/Pages/Diet Center TOC/page_Diet Center_091e9c5e80046694.xml" keywordId="41667" keywordSetId="7928" object_type="wbmd_pb_page" path="/webmd/PageBuilder_Assets/scopemaps/WebMD Consumer/Pages/Diet Center TOC/page_Diet Center_091e9c5e80046694.xml">weight gain</a>, <a chronic_id="091e9c5e80396037" crossLinkId="70837" directive="friendlyurl" externalId="091e9c5e80396037" href="/webmd/consumer_assets/editorial/articles/image_collections/anatomy_pages/picture_of_the_skin.xml" keywordId="60205" keywordSetId="26541" object_type="wbmd_cons_article" path="/webmd/consumer_assets/editorial/articles/image_collections/anatomy_pages/picture_of_the_skin.xml">skin</a> changes, and <a chronic_id="" crossLinkId="43920" directive="friendlyurl" externalId="091e9c5e8001e577" href="/webmd/consumer_assets/controlled_content/healthwise/symptom/Weakness_and_Fatigue-Topic_Overview.xml" keywordId="7389" keywordSetId="1192" object_type="" path="/webmd/consumer_assets/controlled_content/healthwise/symptom/Weakness_and_Fatigue-Topic_Overview.xml">fatigue</a>. It can
			 lead to serious problems, such as
			 <a chronic_id="091e9c5e80024621" crossLinkId="520" directive="friendlyurl" externalId="091e9c5e80024621" href="/webmd/PageBuilder_Assets/scopemaps/WebMD Consumer/Pages/Diabetes Health Center/page_Diabetes Health Center_091e9c5e80024621.xml" keywordId="7249" keywordSetId="1086" object_type="wbmd_pb_page" path="/webmd/PageBuilder_Assets/scopemaps/WebMD Consumer/Pages/Diabetes Health Center/page_Diabetes Health Center_091e9c5e80024621.xml">diabetes</a>,
			 <a chronic_id="091e9c5e800232f5" crossLinkId="536" directive="friendlyurl" externalId="091e9c5e800232f5" href="/webmd/PageBuilder_Assets/scopemaps/WebMD Consumer/Pages/Hypertension Health Center/page_Hypertension Health Center_091e9c5e800232f5.xml" keywordId="36407" keywordSetId="8998" object_type="wbmd_pb_page" path="/webmd/PageBuilder_Assets/scopemaps/WebMD Consumer/Pages/Hypertension Health Center/page_Hypertension Health Center_091e9c5e800232f5.xml">high blood pressure</a>,
			 <a chronic_id="091e9c5e80732fb0" crossLinkId="65" directive="friendlyurl" externalId="091e9c5e80732fb0" href="/webmd/PageBuilder_Assets/scopemaps/WebMD Consumer/Pages/Depression Health Center_091e9c5e80732fb0/page_Depression Health Center_091e9c5e80732fb0.xml" keywordId="7244" keywordSetId="1082" object_type="wbmd_pb_page" path="/webmd/PageBuilder_Assets/scopemaps/WebMD Consumer/Pages/Depression Health Center_091e9c5e80732fb0/page_Depression Health Center_091e9c5e80732fb0.xml">depression</a>, and
			 <a bookmark="sto167501-sec" document-type="Definition" href="/webmd/consumer_assets/controlled_content/healthwise/definition/Osteoporosis.xml" directive="friendlyurl" chronic_id="" object_type="" path="/webmd/consumer_assets/controlled_content/healthwise/definition/Osteoporosis.xml">osteoporosis</a>. If not treated, it can also cause
			 death.  </p><p>Another name for Cushing’s syndrome is
			 hypercortisolism.</p><h4>What causes Cushing's syndrome?</h4><p>Cushing's syndrome
			 may be caused by:</p><ul><li><a bookmark="stc123754-sec" document-type="Definition" href="/webmd/consumer_assets/controlled_content/healthwise/definition/Corticosteroids.xml" directive="friendlyurl" chronic_id="" object_type="" path="/webmd/consumer_assets/controlled_content/healthwise/definition/Corticosteroids.xml"><b>Steroid medicine</b></a>. This medicine
				is used to treat
				<a bookmark="stl158197-sec" document-type="Definition" href="/webmd/consumer_assets/controlled_content/healthwise/definition/Lupus.xml" directive="friendlyurl" chronic_id="" object_type="" path="/webmd/consumer_assets/controlled_content/healthwise/definition/Lupus.xml">lupus</a>,
				<a bookmark="sta123346-sec" document-type="Definition" href="/webmd/consumer_assets/controlled_content/healthwise/definition/Asthma.xml" directive="friendlyurl" chronic_id="" object_type="" path="/webmd/consumer_assets/controlled_content/healthwise/definition/Asthma.xml">asthma</a>,
				<a bookmark="str2414-sec" document-type="Definition" href="/webmd/consumer_assets/controlled_content/healthwise/definition/Rheumatoid_arthritis.xml" directive="friendlyurl" chronic_id="" object_type="" path="/webmd/consumer_assets/controlled_content/healthwise/definition/Rheumatoid_arthritis.xml">rheumatoid arthritis</a>, and other diseases that cause
				inflammation. It may also be used after an <a chronic_id="091e9c5e8063afe6" crossLinkId="1512742" directive="friendlyurl" externalId="091e9c5e8063afe6" href="/webmd/consumer_assets/editorial/articles/health_and_medical_reference/miscellaneous/organ_donation_and_transplant.xml" keywordId="63160" keywordSetId="28660" object_type="wbmd_cons_article" path="/webmd/consumer_assets/editorial/articles/health_and_medical_reference/miscellaneous/organ_donation_and_transplant.xml">organ transplant</a>. Long-term use of
				this medicine is the most common cause of Cushing's syndrome.</li><li><b>Tumors on the pituitary gland.</b> This is called Cushing's
				disease. It’s the second most common cause of Cushing's syndrome. These tumors
				are not <a chronic_id="" crossLinkId="31192" directive="friendlyurl" externalId="9A13E96B1FF14D08" href="http://www.webmd.com/cancer/" keywordId="7043" keywordSetId="942" object_type="" path="/webmdhttp://www.webmd.com/cancer/">cancer</a>.</li><li><b>Tumors on the adrenal glands</b>, or in the <a chronic_id="091e9c5e803c50fe" crossLinkId="72327" directive="friendlyurl" externalId="091e9c5e803c50fe" href="/webmd/consumer_assets/editorial/articles/image_collections/anatomy_pages/picture_of_the_lungs.xml" keywordId="60504" keywordSetId="26698" object_type="wbmd_cons_article" path="/webmd/consumer_assets/editorial/articles/image_collections/anatomy_pages/picture_of_the_lungs.xml">lung</a> or <a chronic_id="091e9c5e8034e371" crossLinkId="70312" directive="friendlyurl" externalId="091e9c5e8034e371" href="/webmd/consumer_assets/editorial/articles/image_collections/anatomy_pages/picture_of_the_pancreas.xml" keywordId="58451" keywordSetId="25860" object_type="wbmd_cons_article" path="/webmd/consumer_assets/editorial/articles/image_collections/anatomy_pages/picture_of_the_pancreas.xml">pancreas</a>. Sometimes these tumors are cancer.
				</li></ul><h4>What are the symptoms?</h4><p><a chronic_id="" crossLinkId="50064" directive="friendlyurl" externalId="091e9c5e8001d084" href="/webmd/consumer_assets/controlled_content/healthwise/special/Healthy_Weight-What_Is_a_Healthy_Weight.xml" keywordId="35927" keywordSetId="8910" object_type="" path="/webmd/consumer_assets/controlled_content/healthwise/special/Healthy_Weight-What_Is_a_Healthy_Weight.xml">Weight</a> gain-especially
			 around the waist-is the most common symptom. </p><p>Cortisol affects
			 almost all body systems, so it can cause many other symptoms. These other
			 symptoms often appear slowly over time and may include:</p><ul><li>Weak muscles. </li><li>Changes in the
				skin, such as bruising,
				<a bookmark="sta123101-sec" document-type="Definition" href="/webmd/consumer_assets/controlled_content/healthwise/definition/Acne.xml" directive="friendlyurl" chronic_id="" object_type="" path="/webmd/consumer_assets/controlled_content/healthwise/definition/Acne.xml">acne</a>, and dark purple-red <a chronic_id="091e9c5e800070d9" crossLinkId="3035" directive="friendlyurl" externalId="091e9c5e800070d9" href="/webmd/consumer_assets/editorial/articles/health_and_medical_reference/skin_and_beauty/cosmetic_procedures/treatment/cosmetic_procedures_stretch_marks.xml" keywordId="40210" keywordSetId="9829" object_type="wbmd_cons_article" path="/webmd/consumer_assets/editorial/articles/health_and_medical_reference/skin_and_beauty/cosmetic_procedures/treatment/cosmetic_procedures_stretch_marks.xml">stretch marks</a> on the
				belly.</li><li>Changes in mood. You may feel irritable, anxious, or
				depressed. </li><li>Extra fat on the back of the neck and upper
				back.</li><li>Backaches.</li><li>Loss of muscle
				tone.</li><li>Irregular
				<a bookmark="stm159394-sec" document-type="Definition" href="/webmd/consumer_assets/controlled_content/healthwise/definition/Menstrual_cycle.xml" directive="friendlyurl" chronic_id="" object_type="" path="/webmd/consumer_assets/controlled_content/healthwise/definition/Menstrual_cycle.xml">menstrual</a> periods.</li><li><a chronic_id="091e9c5e805865cd" crossLinkId="1507668" directive="friendlyurl" externalId="091e9c5e805865cd" href="/webmd/consumer_assets/editorial/articles/image_collections/anatomy_pages/picture_of_the_hair.xml" keywordId="62994" keywordSetId="28549" object_type="wbmd_cons_article" path="/webmd/consumer_assets/editorial/articles/image_collections/anatomy_pages/picture_of_the_hair.xml">Hair</a> growth that is not
				normal (such as facial hair in women).</li><li> High <a chronic_id="091e9c5e80008fa5" crossLinkId="29789" directive="friendlyurl" externalId="091e9c5e80008fa5" href="/webmd/consumer_assets/editorial/articles/health_and_medical_reference/heart_and_blood_vessels/hypertension/overview_types_of/hypertension_blood_pressure_causes.xml" keywordId="31615" keywordSetId="8191" object_type="wbmd_cons_article" path="/webmd/consumer_assets/editorial/articles/health_and_medical_reference/heart_and_blood_vessels/hypertension/overview_types_of/hypertension_blood_pressure_causes.xml">blood pressure</a> and
				high <a chronic_id="091e9c5e802399b9" crossLinkId="56663" directive="friendlyurl" externalId="091e9c5e802399b9" href="/webmd/consumer_assets/editorial/articles/health_and_medical_reference/diabetes/type_2_diabetes/overview_types_of/how_sugar_affects_diabetes.xml" keywordId="42505" keywordSetId="10316" object_type="wbmd_cons_article" path="/webmd/consumer_assets/editorial/articles/health_and_medical_reference/diabetes/type_2_diabetes/overview_types_of/how_sugar_affects_diabetes.xml">blood sugar levels</a>.</li></ul><p>Sometimes <a chronic_id="" crossLinkId="31145" directive="friendlyurl" externalId="AFCA7EE1EFA94E5F" href="http://www.webmd.com/mental-health/tc/Alcohol-Abuse-and-Dependence-Topic-Overview" keywordId="6795" keywordSetId="770" object_type="" path="/webmdhttp://www.webmd.com/mental-health/tc/Alcohol-Abuse-and-Dependence-Topic-Overview">alcoholism</a>, depression,
			 <a bookmark="stp1283-sec" document-type="Definition" href="/webmd/consumer_assets/controlled_content/healthwise/definition/Panic_attack.xml" directive="friendlyurl" chronic_id="" object_type="" path="/webmd/consumer_assets/controlled_content/healthwise/definition/Panic_attack.xml">panic attacks</a>, <a chronic_id="091e9c5e80008af3" crossLinkId="29521" directive="friendlyurl" externalId="091e9c5e80008af3" href="/webmd/consumer_assets/editorial/articles/health_and_medical_reference/healthy_living/diet_and_nutrition/overview_types_of/weight_loss_what_is_obesity.xml" keywordId="7982" keywordSetId="1635" object_type="wbmd_cons_article" path="/webmd/consumer_assets/editorial/articles/health_and_medical_reference/healthy_living/diet_and_nutrition/overview_types_of/weight_loss_what_is_obesity.xml">obesity</a>, or other problems can cause
			 symptoms like these. Some treatments for
			 <a bookmark="sth149894-sec" document-type="Definition" href="/webmd/consumer_assets/controlled_content/healthwise/definition/HIV_human_immunodeficiency_virus.xml" directive="friendlyurl" chronic_id="" object_type="" path="/webmd/consumer_assets/controlled_content/healthwise/definition/HIV_human_immunodeficiency_virus.xml">HIV</a> can also cause similar symptoms. This is called
			 pseudo-Cushing's syndrome. In these cases, symptoms tend to stop as soon as the
			 problems are treated. </p><h4>How is Cushing's syndrome diagnosed?</h4><p>Your doctor
			 will use your medical history, a <a chronic_id="091e9c5e80377b97" crossLinkId="70371" directive="friendlyurl" externalId="091e9c5e80377b97" href="/webmd/consumer_assets/editorial/articles/health_and_medical_reference/miscellaneous/annual_physical_examinations.xml" keywordId="58671" keywordSetId="25958" object_type="wbmd_cons_article" path="/webmd/consumer_assets/editorial/articles/health_and_medical_reference/miscellaneous/annual_physical_examinations.xml">physical exam</a>, and lab tests to see if you
			 have Cushing's syndrome. During the physical exam, he or she will look for
			 signs of the problem. The medical history includes questions about your
			 symptoms, what medicines you take, and-if you are a woman-whether your periods
			 are regular. </p><p>If your doctor thinks you may have Cushing's
			 syndrome, you will have lab tests to check your cortisol levels. These tests
			 can measure cortisol in your blood, urine, or saliva. More tests may be needed
			 to find the cause of high cortisol levels.</p><h4>How is it treated?</h4></section_text></section_group></page><page><section_group><section_header is_continued="true"> continued...</section_header><section_type>Overview</section_type><section_text><p> Cushing’s syndrome can often be
			 cured. But it can lead to serious health problems, including death. So it’s
			 important to start treatment right away. </p><p>If steroid medicine is
			 causing Cushing's syndrome, your doctor will help you lower your dose or
			 gradually stop taking it. It may take a while for the symptoms to go away.
			 </p><p>It’s very dangerous to stop taking steroid medicine on your own.
			 Your doctor will help you change your medicine or lower your dose
			 slowly.</p><p>If a tumor is causing Cushing’s syndrome, you will need
			 surgery to remove it. If surgery doesn't work, <a chronic_id="091e9c5e804d6f9a" crossLinkId="1049001" directive="friendlyurl" externalId="091e9c5e804d6f9a" href="/webmd/consumer_assets/editorial/articles/health_and_medical_reference/cancer/miscellaneous/what_to_expect_from_radiation_therapy.xml" keywordId="61840" keywordSetId="27679" object_type="wbmd_cons_article" path="/webmd/consumer_assets/editorial/articles/health_and_medical_reference/cancer/miscellaneous/what_to_expect_from_radiation_therapy.xml">radiation</a> or <a chronic_id="" crossLinkId="31476" directive="friendlyurl" externalId="09D1C68D81D74991" href="http://www.webmd.com/drugs/index-drugs.aspx" keywordId="34730" keywordSetId="8684" object_type="" path="/webmdhttp://www.webmd.com/drugs/index-drugs.aspx">drugs</a> may be
			 used.</p><p>When you have Cushing’s syndrome, it’s very important to
			 control your weight and keep your bones and muscles strong. This will help
			 prevent diabetes, bone loss, and high blood pressure. Eating healthy foods and
			 staying active can help you do this. </p><p>It’s also important to have
			 regular checkups to look for other problems such as diabetes, high blood
			 pressure, and <a chronic_id="091e9c5e8002487a" crossLinkId="180" directive="friendlyurl" externalId="091e9c5e8002487a" href="/webmd/PageBuilder_Assets/scopemaps/WebMD Consumer/Pages/Osteoporosis Health Center/page_Osteoporosis Health Center_091e9c5e8002487a.xml" keywordId="8007" keywordSetId="1657" object_type="wbmd_pb_page" path="/webmd/PageBuilder_Assets/scopemaps/WebMD Consumer/Pages/Osteoporosis Health Center/page_Osteoporosis Health Center_091e9c5e8002487a.xml">osteoporosis</a>.</p><p><b>Frequently Asked Questions</b></p><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td valign="top"><p><b>Learning about Cushing's syndrome:</b></p></td><td valign="top"><ul><li><a document-type="Mini" href="/webmd/consumer_assets/controlled_content/healthwise/mini/Cushings_Syndrome-Topic_Overview.xml" directive="friendlyurl" chronic_id="091e9c5e8001ab23" object_type="wbmd_cons_article" path="/webmd/consumer_assets/controlled_content/healthwise/mini/Cushings_Syndrome-Topic_Overview.xml">What is Cushing's syndrome?</a></li><li><a document-type="Mini" href="/webmd/consumer_assets/controlled_content/healthwise/mini/Cushings_Syndrome-Topic_Overview.xml" directive="friendlyurl" chronic_id="091e9c5e8001ab23" object_type="wbmd_cons_article" path="/webmd/consumer_assets/controlled_content/healthwise/mini/Cushings_Syndrome-Topic_Overview.xml">What causes it?</a></li><li><a document-type="Mini" href="/webmd/consumer_assets/controlled_content/healthwise/mini/Cushings_Syndrome-Symptoms.xml" directive="friendlyurl" chronic_id="091e9c5e8001ad59" object_type="wbmd_cons_article" path="/webmd/consumer_assets/controlled_content/healthwise/mini/Cushings_Syndrome-Symptoms.xml">What are the symptoms?</a></li><li><a bookmark="ug1738-sec" document-type="Frame" href="/webmd/consumer_assets/controlled_content/healthwise/frame/Who_is_affected_by_Cushings_syndrome.xml" directive="friendlyurl" chronic_id="091e9c5e8001bf42" object_type="wbmd_cons_article" path="/webmd/consumer_assets/controlled_content/healthwise/frame/Who_is_affected_by_Cushings_syndrome.xml">Who is affected by it?</a></li></ul></td></tr><tr><td valign="top"><p><b>Being diagnosed:</b></p></td><td valign="top"><ul><li><a document-type="Mini" href="/webmd/consumer_assets/controlled_content/healthwise/mini/Cushings_Syndrome-Exams_and_Tests.xml" directive="friendlyurl" chronic_id="091e9c5e8001aede" object_type="wbmd_cons_article" path="/webmd/consumer_assets/controlled_content/healthwise/mini/Cushings_Syndrome-Exams_and_Tests.xml">How will my doctor diagnose Cushing's syndrome?</a></li></ul></td></tr><tr><td valign="top"><p><b>Getting treatment:</b></p></td><td valign="top"><ul><li><a document-type="Mini" href="/webmd/consumer_assets/controlled_content/healthwise/mini/Cushings_Syndrome-Treatment_Overview.xml" directive="friendlyurl" chronic_id="091e9c5e8001aec6" object_type="wbmd_cons_article" path="/webmd/consumer_assets/controlled_content/healthwise/mini/Cushings_Syndrome-Treatment_Overview.xml">How is Cushing's syndrome treated?</a></li><li><a document-type="Mini" href="/webmd/consumer_assets/controlled_content/healthwise/mini/Cushings_Syndrome-Treatment_Overview.xml" directive="friendlyurl" chronic_id="091e9c5e8001aec6" object_type="wbmd_cons_article" path="/webmd/consumer_assets/controlled_content/healthwise/mini/Cushings_Syndrome-Treatment_Overview.xml">Will I need surgery?</a></li></ul></td></tr><tr><td valign="top"><p><b>Living with Cushing's syndrome:</b></p></td><td valign="top"><ul><li><a document-type="Mini" href="/webmd/consumer_assets/controlled_content/healthwise/mini/Cushings_Syndrome-Home_Treatment.xml" directive="friendlyurl" chronic_id="091e9c5e8001ae1b" object_type="wbmd_cons_article" path="/webmd/consumer_assets/controlled_content/healthwise/mini/Cushings_Syndrome-Home_Treatment.xml">What can I do to treat Cushing's syndrome at home?</a></li></ul></td></tr></table></section_text></section_group></page></pages><citations></citations></cons_import_health_ref></content_section></wbmd_ass